        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 8 at 11:32AM CDT by NWS Topeka KS</headline>
        <description>At 1131 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 5
miles southwest of Ada, moving southeast at 15 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down twigs or small limbs and blow
around objects. Hail damage to outdoor objects and
vegetation is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Tescott and Ada.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
